<subSubSection box="[199,1370,1480,1505]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,937,1577]" box="[199,1370,1480,1505]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1480,1505]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name reflects the vivid color of the sponge in life, 
<taxonomicName authority="Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[1044,1257,1480,1505]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="aurantiacus">aurantiacus (Latin)</taxonomicName>
= orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="65.[151,1436,937,1577]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1516,1541]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Comments.</emphasis>
In this species the smooth styles replace the tornotes usually encountered in species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1333,1428,1516,1541]" class="Demospongiae" family="Hymedesmiidae" genus="Phorbas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1333,1428,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Phorbas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; the absence of microscleres is within the generic definition.
</paragraph>
